-related%20hemorrhoids.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20she%20got%20screened%20months%20later%2C%20she%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%204%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Gabby%20Zappia%20started%20experiencing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frectal-bleeding-most-common-early-sign-of-colon-cancer-taboo-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblood%20in%20her%20stool%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20her%20obstetrician%20quickly%20reassured%20her.%20She%20was%20six%20months%20into%20her%20third%20pregnancy%20and%20was%20told%20the%20symptom%20was%20likely%20caused%20by%20pregnancy-related%20hemorrhoids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20Zappia%20returned%20to%20her%20busy%20life.%20Caring%20for%20her%20two%20kids%2C%20ages%204%20and%205%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eat%20the%20time%2C%20involved%20nonstop%20carpools%2C%20lunches%2C%20laundry%2C%20and%20dishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20still%20have%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20hard%20time%20slowing%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Zappia%2C%2037%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20before%20her%20due%20date%20in%20June%202024%2C%20Zappia%2C%20who's%20based%20in%20Mission%20Viejo%2C%20California%2C%20saw%20significantly%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprevent-colon-cancer-how-to-tell-poop-is-normal-doctor-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblood%20in%20the%20toilet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20describing%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bblood%20diarrhea.%26quot%3B%20She%20immediately%20went%20to%20OB%20triage%2C%20where%20she%20said%20the%20staff%20seemed%20in%20disbelief%2C%20asking%20her%20if%20she'd%20taken%20any%20photos.%20After%20a%20vaginal%20exam%20found%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20the%20baby%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20induce%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22946%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gabby%20Zappia%20with%20chemo%20port%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a16fe1e2e5a80cfe04ff1e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22709%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZappia%20learned%20she%20had%20late-stage%20colon%20cancer%20just%20months%20after%20giving%20birth.%3Cp%3EGabby%20Zappia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20son's%20birth%2C%20Zappia%20wanted%20to%20focus%20on%20being%20with%20him.%20But%20when%20the%20bleeding%20persisted%2C%20she%20called%20her%20primary%20care%20physician%20and%20was%20put%20on%20a%20three-month%20waiting%20list%20to%20see%20a%20gastroenterologist.%20In%20December%202024%2C%20six%20months%20after%20she%20gave%20birth%2C%20Zappia%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%204%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-rectal-cancer-rise-young-people-protect-yourself-lower-risk-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZappia%2C%20who%20had%20no%20family%20history%20of%20colon%20cancer%2C%20had%20expected%20a%20diagnosis%20like%20polyps%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-misdiagnosis-young-people-ibs-gluten-allergy-symptoms-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECrohn's%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20still%20shocked%2C%20honestly%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20just%20heartbroken.%20I%20thought%20that%20I%20was%20invincible%20before%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2212acba50-2a29-4afe-932f-3c24223831eb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20baseball-sized%20mass%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22984%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gabby%20Zappia%20in%20cancer%20treatment%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a16fb9f2ab5f9757add4c47%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22738%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20mother%20of%20three%20learned%20that%20a%20mass%20was%20nearly%20blocking%20her%20entire%20colon.%3Cp%3EGabby%20Zappia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EZappia%20said%20her%20GI%20was%20the%20first%20time%20she%20felt%20her%20symptom%20was%20being%20taken%20seriously.%20While%20she%20was%20in%20the%20office%2C%20he%20gave%20her%20a%20guaiac-based%20fecal%20occult%20blood%20test%20(gFOBT)%2C%20performed%20on%20a%20card%20that%20turns%20blue%20when%20stool%20samples%20contain%20blood.%20The%20entire%20card%20turned%20blue%2C%20indicating%20a%20higher%20amount%20of%20blood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20scheduled%20her%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-symptoms-in-my-30s-colonoscopy-cost-insurance-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20colonoscopy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20involved%20another%20monthlong%20wait.%20It%20was%20then%2C%20in%20November%202024%2C%20that%20Zappia%20learned%20she%20had%20a%20mass%20so%20big%20that%20it%20nearly%20blocked%20her%20whole%20colon.%20She%20was%20scheduled%20for%20a%20colon%20resection%20surgery%2C%20a%20procedure%20to%20remove%20part%20of%20her%20large%20intestine%2C%20one%20month%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20mass%20was%20the%20size%20of%20a%20baseball%20when%20she%20ended%20up%20taking%20it%20out%2C%20which%20is%20absolutely%20insane%20because%20I'm%20a%20small%20person%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Zappia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224037%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gabby%20Zappia%20pregnant%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a16fbe72ab5f9757add4c4f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223028%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZappia%20made%20an%20effort%20to%20push%20through%20extreme%20fatigue%2C%20thinking%20it%20was%20solely%20related%20to%20pregnancy.%3Cp%3ESara%20Ellen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20put%20in%20perspective%20how%20much%20discomfort%20she%20brushed%20aside%20in%20the%20prior%20months%2C%20including%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-colonoscopy-colon-cancer-symptoms-colorectal-oncologist-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextreme%20fatigue%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20chalked%20up%20to%20pregnancy.%20%26quot%3BThe%20days%20when%20I%20felt%20the%20most%20sick%2C%20like%20I%20was%20in%20thick%20mud%20just%20trying%20to%20get%20my%20day%20started%2C%20were%20the%20days%20that%20I%20pulled%20myself%20together%20the%20most%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZappia%20would%20always%20put%20on%20makeup%20and%20try%20to%20be%20her%20usual%20bubbly%20self%20%E2%80%94%20something%20she%20wonders%20may%20have%20made%20it%20harder%20for%20doctors%20to%20believe%20her.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20was%20kind%20of%20looking%20sick%2C%20maybe%20they%20would've%20been%20more%20concerned%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22952e936d-87f2-40c7-8b62-6f3887756ae0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBalancing%20motherhood%20with%20treatment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223061%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gabby%20Zappia%20with%20her%203%20children%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a16fc3b2e5a80cfe04ff1c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222296%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZappia%20said%20the%20hardest%20part%20of%20treatment%20was%20attending%20to%20her%20children's%20needs%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3Cp%3EJae%20Forsythe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20colon%20resection%20and%20a%20biopsy%20on%20her%20liver%2C%20where%20the%20cancer%20had%20spread%2C%20Zappia%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-30-year-old-son-died-from-colon-cancer-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estage%204%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20she%20had%20healed%20from%20the%20surgery%2C%20Zappia%20underwent%20a%20second%20surgery%20for%20her%20chemotherapy%20port%2C%20which%20provides%20a%20convenient%20access%20point%20for%20chemo%20treatments%2C%20before%20starting%20a%20chemotherapy%20and%20immunotherapy%20regimen.%20In%20between%20those%20treatments%2C%20she%20also%20underwent%20a%20liver%20resection%20and%20ablation%20surgery%20to%20remove%20tumors.%20Zappia%20also%20had%20a%20hepatic%20artery%20infusion%20(HAI)%20pump%20installed%20in%20her%20abdomen%20to%20deliver%20concentrated%20doses%20of%20chemo%20directly%20to%20her%20liver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mom%20of%20three%20young%20children%20said%20the%20hardest%20part%20of%20her%20diagnosis%20was%20being%20a%20patient%20while%20continuing%20to%20be%20an%20engaged%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20a%20mom%2C%20you%20don't%20get%20to%20pause%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYour%20kids%20still%20need%20you.%20They%20still%20want%20snacks.%20They%20still%20want%20you%20to%20be%20there%20for%20bedtime.%26quot%3B%20While%20she%20said%20they%20pushed%20her%20to%20stay%20active%2C%20forcing%20herself%20to%20get%20up%20on%20days%20when%20she%20was%20recovering%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-mild-cramps-colon-cancer-diagnosed-colonoscopy-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echemo%20side%20effects%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20bone%20pain%20and%20flu-like%20symptoms%2C%20it%20still%20made%20her%20experience%20extra%20challenging.%20For%20example%2C%20she%20was%20afraid%20to%20hold%20her%20kids%20out%20of%20fear%20of%20them%20accidentally%20pulling%20the%20tubing%20of%20her%20chemo%20pump%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20difficult%20to%20find%20childcare%20on%20days%20she%20was%20at%20the%20hospital.%20Still%2C%20she%20had%20her%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22989%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gabby%20Zappia%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20Mike.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a16fc9bb4fb977f3598015c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22742%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZappia%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20Mike.%3Cp%3EGabby%20Zappia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20so%20incredibly%20lucky%20to%20have%20an%20amazing%20husband%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20who%20handled%20nearly%20all%20of%20her%20household%20and%20childcare%20responsibilities%20throughout%20treatment.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20tried%20to%20tackle%20this%20as%20a%20team%20and%20work%20hard%20to%20normalize%20life%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20for%20the%20kids%2C%20keep%20things%20routine%2C%20celebrate%20the%20little%20things%2C%20and%20just%20make%20sure%20our%20home%20still%20feels%20safe%20and%20full%20of%20joy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriends%2C%20family%2C%20neighbors%2C%20and%20people%20from%20Zappia's%20church%20also%20chipped%20in%20to%20help%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrue-cost-young-colon-cancer-crisis-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecarpools%20and%20meals%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20does%20take%20a%20village%2C%20and%20we've%20really%20needed%20to%20lean%20on%20them%20throughout%20this%20whole%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22de9d25d4-763e-4e20-8fc6-ee44f99390d6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBumps%20in%20treatment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221179%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gabby%20Zappia%20in%20cancer%20treatment%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a16fd032ab5f9757add4c6c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22884%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20she%20was%20done%20with%20treatment%2C%20a%20PET%20scan%20found%20new%20cancer%20activity%20in%20Zappia's%20liver.%3Cp%3EGabby%20Zappia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20liver%20resection%2C%20Zappia%20finished%20chemotherapy%20and%20rang%20the%20bell%20in%20September%202025%20after%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-dismissed-doctors-years-diagnosed-stage-3-colon-cancer-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20evidence%20of%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20an%20incredible%20milestone%20in%20my%20journey%2C%20but%20early%2C%26quot%3B%20Zappia%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20months%20later%2C%20a%20PET%20scan%20found%20some%20cancer%20activity%20in%20her%20liver.%20After%20the%20initial%20shock%20of%20her%20new%20diagnosis%20wore%20off%2C%20Zappia%20said%20she%20realized%20she'd%20have%20%26quot%3Bbumps%20in%20the%20road.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20just%20important%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20I%20can%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZappia%20underwent%20a%20robotic%20liver%20resection%20at%20the%20end%20of%202025%20to%20remove%20the%20affected%20area.%20But%20after%20an%20MRI%20revealed%20a%20new%20tumor%20nearby%2C%20she%20had%20the%20procedure%20again%20in%20March%202026%20%E2%80%94%20marking%20her%20third%20liver%20surgery%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20multiple%20surgeries%2C%20her%20blood%20tests%20found%20no%20signs%20of%20disease%20as%20of%20April%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gabby%20Zappia%20with%20her%20family.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a16fd832e5a80cfe04ff1db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222286%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZappia%20with%20her%20family.%3Cp%3EJae%20Forsythe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20colorectal%20cancer%20is%20now%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-leading-cause-cancer-death-under-50-shocking-experts-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeadliest%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20people%20under%2050%2C%20Zappia%20believes%20people%20should%20be%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20symptoms%20like%20bloody%20stools%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20common%20signs%20of%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSure%2C%20it%20might%20be%20hemorrhoids%2C%20and%20that%20would%20be%20awesome%2C%20but%20confirm%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Zappia%20said.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20just%20take%20the%20possibility%20that%20that's%20what%20it%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-colon-cancer-symptom-dismissed-pregnancy-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780946247000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a16fef12e5a80cfe04ff1f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-colon-cancer-symptom-dismissed-pregnancy-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gabby%20Zappia%2C%2037%2C%20experienced%20blood%20in%20her%20stool%20during%20her%20third%20pregnancy.%20Months%20after%20giving%20birth%2C%20she%20learned%20she%20had%20stage%204%20colon%20cancer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpugachevsky%40businessinsider.com%20(Julia%20Pugachevsky)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dalit%20Teen%20Beaten%20To%20Death%20Over%20Inter-Caste%20Friendship%20In%20Uttarakhand%3A%20Cops%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22An%2018-year-old%20Dalit%20youth%20was%20allegedly%20beaten%20to%20death%20and%20his%20friend%20severely%20injured%20over%20his%20friendship%20with%20a%20minor%20girl%20from%20an%20upper%20caste%20community%20in%20the%20Pratapnagar%20block%20here%2C%20police%20said%20on%20Monday.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780946191000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdalit-teen-beaten-to-death-over-inter-caste-friendship-in-uttarakhand-cops-11609617%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%2018-year-old%20Dalit%20youth%20was%20allegedly%20beaten%20to%20death%20and%20his%20friend%20severely%20injured%20over%20his%20friendship%20with%20a%20minor%20girl%20from%20an%20upper%20caste%20community%20in%20the%20Pratapnagar%20block%20here%2C%20police%20said%20on%20Monday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdalit-teen-beaten-to-death-over-inter-caste-friendship-in-uttarakhand-cops-11609617%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww